    <item>
      <title>Video Games</title>
      <link>https://christian.kuendig.info/tags/video-games/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 09 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://christian.kuendig.info/tags/video-games/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve always loved video games. From LAN parties in the early 2000s to working in the industry, gaming has been a constant thread through my life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;float-right&#34;&gt;
    &lt;img loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;https://christian.kuendig.info/tags/video-games/15033503-AA83-407F-B753-B397AD3FCF47_1_102_a.jpeg  &#34;
         alt=&#34;The Shark Dash team in Hanoi&#34; width=&#34;300&#34;/&gt; &lt;figcaption&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;15033503-AA83-407F-B753-B397AD3FCF47_1_102_a.jpeg&#34;&gt;Shark Dash Team at Gameloft Hanoi Studio, Oct 2014&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In 2014, I moved to Vietnam and joined Gameloft as a game producer in their Hanoi studio. I managed teams of a variety of sizes and spent many nights coordinating releases. It also got me a
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.mobygames.com/person/714265/christian-kuendig/&#34;&gt;MobyGames&lt;/a&gt; profile.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Home Automation</title>
      <link>https://christian.kuendig.info/tags/home-automation/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 10 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://christian.kuendig.info/tags/home-automation/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I try to tinker with gadgets around the house. Mostly because it&amp;rsquo;s fun to work on things that have a connection to the physical world. To that end, I&amp;rsquo;m also maintaining a few open source projects:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;home-assistant-custom-components&#34;&gt;Home Assistant Custom Components&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/chkuendig/hass-amphiro-ble&#34;&gt;Amphiro Digital Hand Shower&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; – Reads sensor data from the Amphiro Digital Hand Shower via Bluetooth for tracking water and energy usage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://my.home-assistant.io/redirect/hacs_repository/?owner=chkuendig&amp;amp;repository=hass-amphiro-ble&amp;amp;category=integration&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Install with HACS&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;https://christian.kuendig.info/tags/home-automation/hacs_badge.svg&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/chkuendig/hass-ab_ble_gateway&#34;&gt;April Brother (AB) BLE Gateway V4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; – Forwards BLE advertisement data from the April Brother BLE Gateway V4 to Home Assistant&amp;rsquo;s Bluetooth integration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
